  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "c0tbaQGjTF0jG0Oz1e5FFzTEPbs=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "# never import error classes manually in reducer code\n\n```typescript\n// \u274c Don't manually import error classes\nimport { MissingIdError } from \"../../gen/module-name/error.js\";\nthrow new MissingIdError(\"message\");\n\n// \u274c Don't use nested access patterns\nthrow new errors.ModuleName.MissingIdError(\"message\");\n\n// \u2705 Just reference the error by name \u2014 auto-imported\nthrow new MissingIdError(\"message\");\n```\n\nSince [[error classes in reducers are auto-imported by name reference]], the code generator scans for error class names and inserts the correct imports. Manual imports conflict with auto-generated ones, creating duplicate import errors or path mismatches.\n\n---\n\nTopics:\n- [[reducer patterns]]\n- [[gotchas]]",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:37.000Z"
    }
  },
